  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study will assess the safety and efficacy of escalating doses INC280 when added to
      gefitinib in patients with lung cancer that are known to have dysregulation of the c-MET
      pathway and who have failed after benefiting on a prior treatment with either gefitinib or
      erlotinib.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Patients will be treated INC280 and gefitinib(250mg) daily. Dose escalation for INC280 will
      be performed. Each cohort for the phase IB part will consist of 3 to 6 newly enrolled
      patients. A twice daily administration of INC280 may be investigated if deemed appropriate
      based on emerging results from ongoing clinical trials.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
